## Summary of 6 Storage Modules

### 1. `charity-storage.ts` — Charity/Nonprofit (ProPublica)

- __Prisma models:__ `CanonicalEntity` (charities), `EntityIdentifier` (ein), `CharityProfile`, `EntityAlias`, `CharityFiling`, `RawArtifact`, `FraudSignalEvent`, `FraudSnapshot`
- __Data:__ Nonprofit profiles (EIN, address, classification), 990 tax filings (revenue/expense breakdown, ratios, assets/liabilities), artifact references, fraud signals/snapshots
- __Key functions:__ `persistCharityComputation(record, options)` — main entry point for entity+filing+signal+snapshot persistence

### 2. `consumer-storage.ts` — Consumer Complaints (CFPB)

- __Prisma models:__ `CanonicalEntity` (consumer), `EntityIdentifier` (consumer_company_name), `ConsumerComplaintRecord`, `ConsumerCompanySummary`
- __Data:__ Individual complaints (company, product, issue, narrative, response, timeliness, dispute flag) and per-company aggregated summaries
- __Key functions:__ `parseConsumerComplaintRecord(record)` — parses CSV/JSON rows; `persistConsumerComplaintBatch(rows, sourcePublishedAt)` — batch upsert with summary refresh

### 3. `corporate-storage.ts` — Corporate/SEC EDGAR

- __Prisma models:__ `CanonicalEntity` (corporate), `EntityIdentifier` (sec_cik/sec_ticker), `CorporateCompanyProfile`, `CorporateFilingRecord`, `CorporateCompanyFactsSnapshot`
- __Data:__ Company profiles (CIK, tickers, SIC, incorporation state), filing records (accession number, dates, form type), full EDGAR facts JSON
- __Key functions:__ `persistCorporateTickerUniverse(entries)` — seed from ticker index; `persistCorporateSubmissions(submissions)` — persist submission page+filing records; `persistCorporateCompanyFacts(cik, facts)` — store facts JSON snapshot

### 4. `healthcare-storage.ts` — Healthcare Payments (CMS Open Payments)

- __Prisma models:__ `CanonicalEntity` (healthcare, recipient/payer), `EntityIdentifier` (cms_recipient_key/cms_recipient_profile_id/cms_recipient_npi/cms_payer_name), `HealthcarePaymentRecord`, `HealthcareRecipientProfile`
- __Data:__ Physician-manufacturer payment records (type, year, amount, nature, date) and physician profiles (name, specialty, NPI, location)
- __Key functions:__ `fetchCmsOpenPaymentsDatasets()` — resolve dataset catalog; `parseHealthcarePaymentRecord(params)` / `parseHealthcareRecipientSupplementRecord(record)` — parse raw rows; `persistHealthcarePaymentBatch(params)` — batch upsert payments+profiles; `persistHealthcareRecipientSupplementBatch(params)` — profile-only upsert

### 5. `political-storage.ts` — Political/Campaign Finance (FEC)

- __Prisma models:__ `CanonicalEntity` (political, candidate/committee), `EntityIdentifier` (fec_candidate_id/fec_committee_id), `PoliticalCandidateProfile`, `PoliticalCommitteeProfile`, `PoliticalCycleSummary`
- __Data:__ Candidate profiles (name, party, office, state/district), committee profiles (type, designation, treasurer, linked candidates, cycles), per-cycle financial totals (receipts, disbursements, contributions, cash on hand, debts)
- __Key functions:__ `persistPoliticalCandidateBatch(candidates)` / `persistPoliticalCommitteeBatch(committees)` — entity+profile upsert; `persistPoliticalTotals(params)` / `persistPoliticalTotalsBatch(params)` — financial totals upsert

### 6. `government-storage.ts` — Government Contracts (USAspending)

- __Prisma models:__ `CanonicalEntity` (government, recipient), `EntityIdentifier` (usaspending_recipient_name), `GovernmentAwardRecord`
- __Data:__ Federal award records (award ID, recipient, awarding agency, amounts, dates, type) enriched with detail (UEI, business categories, NAICS/PSC, contract pricing, performance location)
- __Key functions:__ `persistGovernmentAwardSummaries(awards, sourceUpdatedAt)` — batch upsert summaries; `persistGovernmentAwardDetail(generatedInternalId, award)` — enrich with full API detail

### Cross-cutting patterns

- All modules create `CanonicalEntity` + `EntityIdentifier` pairs with domain-specific identifier types
- Each defines a `*_SOURCE_SYSTEM_ID` constant for traceability
- All persistence is wrapped in `prisma.$transaction` with idempotent upserts
- Only charity storage integrates with fraud scoring (`FraudSignalEvent` + `FraudSnapshot`)

