## ARCHITECTURE.md (129 lines)

Describes TrackFraud's __single-backend architecture__ with Next.js 15 handling both frontend and API layer.

__System Stack:__

- __Frontend:__ Next.js 15.5.15, React 19.1.0, Tailwind CSS 3.4.1, TypeScript 5.9.3
- __Backend:__ Next.js API Routes, Prisma 6.14.0, Zod 4.3.6 validation
- __Data:__ PostgreSQL 16 (53 models, ~2.4M records), Meilisearch v1.10 (6 indexes), Redis 7 (caching)
- __DevOps:__ Docker Compose, GitHub Actions CI/CD, Sentry, Vitest + Playwright

__Data Flow:__

```javascript
User Request → Next.js API Route → Prisma → PostgreSQL
                                ↓
                          Meilisearch (search)
                                ↓
                          Redis (cache)
                                ↓
                          Sentry (errors)
```

__Key decisions:__ Single backend (Python/FastAPI eliminated), Prisma pruned from 81→53 models, fraud scoring in TypeScript only.

__API Routes:__ `/api/charities/*`, `/api/corporate/*`, `/api/government/*`, `/api/political/*`, `/api/healthcare/*`, `/api/consumer/*`, `/api/search`, `/api/fraud-scores`, `/api/health`

