## `lib/ingestion-utils.ts` — Data Ingestion Runtime

Handles the full lifecycle of downloading raw data files and recording them in the database:

- __File download with versioning__ (`downloadVersionedFile`): Fetches files by URL, organizes into `year/version_date/` directories, skips cached copies, computes SHA-256 checksums during streaming. Strips macOS provenance attributes.
- __Checksum + size computation__ (`checksumFile`): Pipes files through Node streams for SHA-256 and byte count without full memory load.
- __Database retry with backoff__ (`withDatabaseRetry`): Wraps Prisma operations in exponential backoff + jitter (up to 6 retries) for transient errors (connection failures, P1001/P1002/P1008/P1017).
- __Ingestion run bookkeeping__ (`startIngestionRun`, `finishIngestionRun`, `failIngestionRun`): Creates `IngestionRun` records, updates `SourceSystem` timestamps, writes row-level stats (inserted/updated/skipped/failed).
- __Artifact persistence__ (`upsertRawArtifact`): Upserts `RawArtifact` records keyed by `storageKey`, linking downloads to source systems, runs, and entity IDs.
- __JSON snapshot writer__ (`writeJsonSnapshot`): Serializes payloads to disk with checksum tracking.

__Bottom line:__ The plumbing layer — download, hash, persist, and track every ingestion pass.

