## `lib/warehouse.ts` — Normalization & Enrichment Utilities

A small collection of pure helper functions for cleaning raw data before it enters the canonical store:

- __Entity name normalization__ (`normalizeEntityName`): NFKD Unicode normalization → strip non-word chars → collapse whitespace → uppercase. Used for fuzzy matching/entity resolution.
- __Text compacting__ (`compactText`): Collapse whitespace, trim, return `null` for empty strings.
- __Type coercion__ (`parseOptionalDate`, `parseOptionalNumber`): Safe parsing from mixed input (string/number/Date), returning `null` on failure.
- __Date comparison__ (`latestDate`): Returns most recent date from variadic mixed inputs.
- __Mirror metadata attachment__ (`withMirrorMetadata`): Tags payloads with `dataSource` ("local"/"live"/"merged"), freshness timestamp, and coverage status for provenance tracking.

__Bottom line:__ The normalization layer — turns messy raw fields into clean, comparable canonical values with provenance metadata.

