## `lib/signals.ts` — Fraud Signal Generation

The rule-based engine converting computed financial metrics into structured risk signals:

- __IRS classification lookup__ (`SUBSECTION_LABELS`, `FORM_TYPE_LABELS`, `buildLegalClassification`): Maps IRS 501(c) codes and form types (990/990-EZ/990-PF) to labels. Detects private foundations (Form 990-PF).

- __Risk signal generation__ (`buildRiskSignals`): Evaluates three financial ratios against thresholds from `lib/policy.ts`, producing `RiskSignal[]` with severity ("medium" | "high"):

  1. __Low program spending ratio__ — warn < 0.7, high < 0.55
  2. __High fundraising cost__ — warn > 0.25, high > 0.50
  3. __High officer compensation share__ — warn > 0.10, high > 0.18

- Each signal carries `key`, `label`, `severity`, `detail`, `value`, and `threshold` for transparency.

__Bottom line:__ The detection layer — takes normalized metrics, compares against policy thresholds, emits structured severity-graded fraud risk signals.

